<refentry xml:id="function.harudoc-reseterror" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
 <refnamediv>
  <refname>HaruDoc::resetError</refname>
  <refpurpose>Reset error state of the document handle</refpurpose>
 </refnamediv>

 <refsect1 role="description">
  &reftitle.description;
  <methodsynopsis>
   <type>bool</type><methodname>HaruDoc::resetError</methodname>
   <void/>
  </methodsynopsis>
  <para>
   Once an error code is set, most of the operations, including I/O processing
   functions cannot be performed. In case if you want to continue after the cause 
   of the error has been fixed, you have to invoke this function in order to
   reset the document error state.
  </para>
 </refsect1>

 <refsect1 role="returnvalues">
  &reftitle.returnvalues;
  <para>
   Always succeedes and returns &true;.
  </para>
 </refsect1>

</refentry>

